  "cooking_instructions": [
    {
      "instruction": "<p>Preheat the oven to 220°C/ 200°C (fan)/ gas 7</p><p>Cut your<strong> aubergine[s]</strong> in half lengthways (including the stalk[s]), then score the <strong>aubergine flesh</strong> with a sharp knife in a criss-cross pattern, taking care not to cut through to the skin, then rub the flesh with a drizzle of <strong>olive oil</strong></p><p>Add the <strong>scored aubergine halves</strong> to a baking tray (or two!), cut-side down, and put the tray[s] in the oven for 25-30 min or until the flesh is tender and golden brown</p>",
