            "width": 1500
          }
        ]
      }
    },
    {
      "instruction": "<p>While the rice is cooking, peel and slice your<strong> red onion[s] </strong>finely</p><p>Heat a large, wide-based pan (preferably non-stick with a matching lid) with a drizzle of <strong>olive oil</strong> over a medium-high heat</p><p>Once hot, add the <strong>sliced onion</strong> with a pinch of <strong>salt </strong>and <strong>sugar </strong>and cook for 6-7 min or until softened</p>",
      "order": 3,
      "media": {
        "images": [
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/step-3-1696241156445-x200.jpg",
            "width": 200
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/step-3-1696241156445-x400.jpg",
            "width": 400
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/step-3-1696241156445-x700.jpg",
            "width": 700
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/step-3-1696241156445-x1000.jpg",
            "width": 1000
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/step-3-1696241156445-x1500.jpg",
            "width": 1500
          }
        ]
      }
    },
    {
      "instruction": "<p>Meanwhile, chop your <strong>tomato[es] </strong>into bite-sized pieces</p><p>Peel and finely chop (or grate) your <strong>garlic</strong></p><p>Crush your <strong>walnuts</strong> in their bag with a <strong>rolling pin</strong> (keep them in the bag so you don't lose any!)</p><p>Tip: If you don’t have a rolling pin, just chop them roughly!</p><p>Chop your <strong>parsley</strong> finely, including the stalks</p>",
      "order": 4,
      "media": {
        "images": [
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/step-4-1696241159773-x200.jpg",
            "width": 200
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/step-4-1696241159773-x400.jpg",
            "width": 400
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/step-4-1696241159773-x700.jpg",
            "width": 700
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/step-4-1696241159773-x1000.jpg",
            "width": 1000
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/step-4-1696241159773-x1500.jpg",
            "width": 1500
          }
        ]
      }
    },
    {
      "instruction": "<p>Once the onion has softened, add the <strong>chopped garlic</strong> and <strong>chopped tomato</strong> to the pan and cook for 4-5 min or until the tomatoes have softened</p><p>Once softened, add your <strong>balsamic sun-dried tomato paste</strong> to the pan with <strong>half </strong>your <strong>vegetable stock mix </strong>(save the rest for later!), <strong>dried basil</strong> and a generous pinch of <strong>salt</strong></p><p>Cook for 1 min or until fragrant, then crumble <strong>half</strong> your <strong>goats’ cheese</strong> (you’ll use the rest later!) into the pan, stir it all together and keep covered – this is your<strong> stuffing</strong></p>",
      "order": 5,
      "media": {
        "images": [
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/step-5-1696241163686-x200.jpg",
            "width": 200
